writes – out in the world: No matter what your ethnic background or gender might be, you can spread HIV even if you don’t know you have HIV. People in the U.S. who look young and healthy can have the most advanced HIV. The more we learn about HIV, hopefully we can stop the spread of this deadly virus.

There are several ways of testing and diagnosing HIV infection. For people with identified risk factors for HIV, it is best to start with a quick, rapid HIV test. For those without such documented risk factors, starting with an oral HIV test may be best.
